SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 37-3-703(d), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting:
(d) The state of Tennessee shall conduct ongoing evaluations of the healthy
start pilot project and publish data on or before December 31 of each year. Each state
agency that provides services to children shall make available nonidentifying information
about healthy start participants for the purpose of conducting the evaluation. The report
must include the following information for the preceding fiscal year:
(1) The number of families receiving services through the project;
(2) The average cost of services provided under the project;
(3) The performance measures achieved by program participants; and
(4) An overall statement of the achievements and progress of the project
during the preceding fiscal year, along with recommendations for improvement or
expansion.
